article_title: Target says SEC doesn't plan to bring charges over data breach
article_text: The Securities and Exchange Commission's enforcement division does not plan to bring charges against Target TGT, +0.86% over its 2013 data breach. The retailer disclosed the SEC's intentions in a 10-Q filing. Target is still facing private litigation as well as investigations from states attorneys general and the Federal Trade Commission.

article_metadata.author: Steve Goldstein
